headlines.description: — Moritz Wagner had 22 points, his younger brother, Franz, added 14 and the Orlando Magic returned from the All-Star break to beat Cleveland 116-109 on Thursday night, handing the Cavaliers just their third loss in 21 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Moritz Wagner scores 22, Magic reserves shine in 116-109 win over Cavs without All-Star Mitchell

headlines.description: — All-Star point guard Tyrese Haliburton had 25 points and 13 assists to help the Indiana Pacers beat the NBA-worst Detroit Pistons 129-115 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Haliburton has 25 points and 13 assists in Pacers' 129-115 victory over Pistons

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson heard “MVP!” chants each time the New York Knicks All-Star stepped to the free-throw line. The former Villanova All-American signed dozens of autographs before the game — many for fans wearing his old college jersey.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Brunson, Knicks spoil Kyle Lowry's 76ers debut with Spike Lee watching in Philly, win 110-96

headlines.description: — Scottie Barnes had 18 points and 12 rebounds, Gary Trent Jr. scored 25 points and the Toronto Raptors beat Brooklyn 121-93 on Thursday night, spoiling the debut of interim Nets coach Kevin Ollie.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes scores 18, Raptors beat the Nets and spoil debut of Brooklyn interim coach Kevin Ollie

headlines.description: — The longest winning streak of the season for the Dallas Mavericks coincides with a tie for the longest stretch of games together for the star pairing of Luka Doncic and Kyrie Irving.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 41 points, pairs with Irving to help Mavs beat Suns 123-113 for 7th straight victory

headlines.description: — The Boston Celtics enjoyed their break and were ready to get back to work. The NBA leaders got the job done in another convincing win.
headlines.shortLinkText: White and Tatum team to help Celtics beat Bulls 129-112 for season-high 7th straight win

events.name: Houston Rockets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson had 27 points and nine assists, and the New Orleans Pelicans defeated the struggling Houston Rockets 127-105 on Thursday night for their eighth victory in nine games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson has 27 points, 9 assists as Pelicans pound Rockets 127-105

events.name: LA Clippers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 31 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Los Angeles Clippers 129-107 on Thursday night in a matchup of Western Conference contenders.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scores 31 points, Thunder beat Clippers 129-107

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic became the third player in NBA history to record at least one triple-double against every opponent in the league, going 10-for-10 from the floor and finishing with 21...
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic's triple-double in 130-110 win over Wizards gives him at least one against every opponent

headlines.description: — Miles Bridges had 26 points and 14 rebounds, Grant Williams scored 24 points and the Charlotte Hornets shot past the Utah Jazz 115-107 on Thursday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miles Bridges has 26 points and 14 rebounds, Hornets beat Jazz for 4th straight victory

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry started hitting big shots from the start and the Golden State Warriors dominated the Lakers without LeBron James, helping take at least some of the sting out of a double-overtime collapse when the California rivals met last month.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 32 points as Warriors beat Lakers team missing LeBron James, 128-110

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had his NBA-leading 19th triple-double with 22 points, 11 assists and 11 rebounds, De’Aaron Fox added 28 points and nine assists and the Sacramento Kings beat the San Antonio Spurs 127-122 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Domantas Sabonis has 19th triple-double to help Kings beat Spurs 127-122
